00:19:10.090 --> 00:19:10.881
STEVEN COOK: Right.

00:19:10.881 --> 00:19:12.760
The heat from the motor
actually your friend.

00:19:12.760 --> 00:19:15.344
If you take cold hummus out of
the refrigerator, it seizes up.

00:19:15.344 --> 00:19:17.551
You put it back in here,
maybe a little bit of water,

00:19:17.551 --> 00:19:19.470
and just, literally, the
warmth from the motor

00:19:19.470 --> 00:19:21.344
is going to bring it
back to room temperature

00:19:21.344 --> 00:19:23.085
and make it taste
like you just made it.

